## 3. Submission sequence (artifact-readiness view)

1. **Prove the surfaces + stand up scanning** — package compiles in a
   namespaced environment (unblocks Code Analyzer); endpoint reachable in
   production mode; SSL Labs + DAST runnable. Gate: every §1.2/§1.3 row is at
   least PARTIAL with a named closer.
2. **Review prep** — scans run + remediated/documented; FP dossier complete;
   test environment stood up; questionnaire owner-confirmed; business items
   (§1.6) executed. Gate: zero TODO rows without an in-flight owner.
3. **Submit** — wizard transcription (questionnaire §K reconciliation), fee,
   contacts. Timing expectations are perishable — read
   `process-review-timeline` at fill time (verified: a total measured from
   receipt of a COMPLETE submission, with a stage decomposition for
   verification / first-time testing / resubmission); plan from the
   baseline, not from this document.

